title: Untitled Goose Game Can't Be Stopped - Kinda Funny Games Daily 03.19.20
description:
Blessing and Tim talk about another game of the year win for Untitled Goose Game along with more Black Ops rumors. 

Time Stamps - 
00:02:55 - Housekeeping
The Kinda Funny Community Social Distancing Smash Tournament IS HAPPENING this Saturday! Go to twitter.com/kindaNYC and check their pinned tweet for the sign up link!
We were supposed to host the Core Reveal Party this week on Kinda Funny, but working from home means that can’t happen. We will do a big stream where we play Core with you and build multiplayer games, but that isn’t happening this week. Instead, support Core! They’re in alpha and you can sign up to create your own multiplayer games and play them instantly with the world! Go to CoreGames.com for get in the alpha, get creating, and get ready for our stream. Plus, you can catch the team streaming on twitch.tv/corelive.
Thank you to our Patreon Producers: Mohammed Mohammed, Drew Gardiner, Black Jack, The Kinda Funny Destiny 2 PC Clan
The Roper Report   -
00:04:44 - Untitled Goose Game wins GDC Game of the Year
00:13:45 - Is the Xbox Series X Releasing during Thanksgiving? - Rebekah Valentine @ GIBiz
00:20:00 - Do you feel PlayStation 5 so far is just kinda just dull and boring?  - Best Friends Q:Quickjab
00:23:06 - More Call of Duty Black Ops Rumors Continue to surface - Tom Ivan @ Video Games Chronicle
00:30:10 - Gamestop’s Selling Doom Eternal early - GS Twitter
00:31:00 - The developers of The Messenger have revealed their next game!
00:34:29 - Introducing Xbox Game Pass Ultimate
00:37:30 - Out today
00:44:38 -  HIMS
00:46:26 - Manscaped
 Reader mail   -
00:48:36 - With the Final Fantasy 7 Remake release looming, I, as an Xbox owner with no PS4, am feeling a little bummed out since I won’t be able to play. I have to wonder, what does a AAA game developer like Square Enix gain from timed exclusivity? - Demon King Oda
00:52:48 - Letter GameStop employee- Michael
01:00:38 - Squad Up: Online tutoring assistance squad up: @DaNanoBiologist
01:02:08- You‘re Wrong
Tomorrow’s Hosts:Greg & Blessing
